40|$|An {{area has}} been mapped in detail in the {{vicinity}} of the Box property ih the Goldfields district. The oldest formations are quartzites, dolomites, and various schists and gneisses. These are cut by granites and gabbros. The distribution and metamorphism of the rocks of the area are described. Cooke has considered the gabbro as younger than the granite, but the <b>writer</b> <b>agrees</b> with Alcock in considering the granite younger than the gabbro. The problem of the "Box granite" is discussed. The writer has shown that this" formation is composite, and has separated. on. the map gr. anitized sedimentary rocks from granites...|$|R
50|$|They reached land {{in early}} October after over two {{months on the}} ice, setting foot on Kvitøya (White Island), just east of Svalbard. They perished there, {{probably}} within two weeks after landfall. Most modern <b>writers</b> <b>agree</b> that Nils Strindberg died {{within a week of}} arrival: he was buried among the rocks (though no marker was placed on his grave) while the other two men were later found in the tent.|$|E
